Leadership
The Platinum Equity Partners and Principals are a driving force behind Platinum Equity’s continuity, consistency, and shared
vision. The Partners and Principals lead in-house teams and guide every facet of the firm’s strategy, from investment theses and deal processes to portfolio development and financial management.















































Tom Gores
Chairman & CEO
Tom Gores founded Platinum Equity in 1995 and his guidance, core philosophies, and strong principles drive the strategic development and direction of both Platinum and its portfolio.
Read more...
“The ability to move on multiple fronts concurrently has been one of the single biggest factors to our success.”



Mary Ann Sigler
Chief Financial Officer
Mary Ann Sigler  is responsible for overall accounting, tax, and financial reporting as well as managing strategic planning projects for Platinum Equity. In addition to these responsibilities, Ms. Sigler is the firm’s Chief Compliance Officer. 
Read more...



Mark Barnhill
Partner
Mark Barnhill manages functions connected to capital raising, fund administration, and corporate and external affairs for Platinum. He also is the senior relationship manager with Platinum’s investors. 
Read more...



John Diggins
Partner
John Diggins is responsible for senior level business development efforts at Platinum, as well as growing the revenue base of Platinum’s operating companies and identifying opportunities for them to build market advantages. 
Read more...



Eva Kalawski
Partner, General Counsel and Secretary
Eva Kalawski  oversees Platinum’s in-house legal staff and is responsible for addressing legal issues relating to diligence, M&A, and transitions, as well as the legal affairs of its portfolio companies. 
Read more...



Bryan Kelln
Partner
Bryan Kelln  is President of Portfolio Operations and is responsible for all aspects of business strategy and operations at Platinum Equity’s portfolio companies. 
Read more...



Jacob Kotzubei
Partner
Jacob Kotzubei is a Partner and member of Platinum Equity’s Investment Committee, leads a Los Angeles-based investment team and has oversight responsibility for investment teams in Europe and Asia. In addition, Mr. Kotzubei plays a substantial role in raising capital from limited partners for the firm’s investment funds.
Read more...



Johnny Lopez
Partner
Johnny O. Lopez is a member of Platinum’s Investment Committee, continues to actively pursue significant M&A transactions across multiple industries, mentors transaction teams, and is increasingly involved in the firm’s business development efforts. Mr. Lopez is also a lead sponsor of Platinum’s investment in public securities for control.
Read more...



Philip Norment
Partner
Phil Norment is a member of Platinum’s Investment Committee and is a senior advisor on specific operational initiatives throughout the portfolio. He is also the senior executive responsible for evaluating acquisition opportunities and integrating new acquisitions into the portfolio. 
Read more...



Louis Samson
Partner

Louis Samson leads Platinum Equity’s New York and London-based
investment teams, manages the operations of the New York and London offices,
and is a member of the Investment Committee. In his role, Mr. Samson oversees
all financial, operating, tax, and legal aspects of M&A transactions
executed by his team. Additionally, together with the Operations Team, he
provides oversight to the portfolio companies for which he led the acquisition.

Read more...



Robert Wentworth
Partner
Robert Wentworth participates in senior level M&A activities for Platinum Equity and is a member of the Investment Committee. 
Read more...



Bob Wymbs
Partner

Bob Wymbs leads Platinum Equity’s buy-side M&A team focused on the lower middle
market as well as the firm’s dedicated sell-side team.
Read more...



Dave Aroesty
Principal
Dave Aroesty is responsible for evaluating operational turnaround 
opportunities in the hospitality industry and other sectors in which real estate 
provides a strong element of downside protection to the investment thesis.
Read more...



Craig Ashmore
Principal
Craig Ashmore is responsible for senior level business development activities focused on identifying new acquisition opportunities. 
Read more...



Stephanie Barter
Principal
Stephanie Barter oversees Platinum Equity’s in-house M&A Operations group, a team comprising functional experts across a wide range of operational disciplines that conducts due diligence on prospective acquisitions.
Read more...



David C. Boutry
Principal
David C. Boutry is Global Head of Business Development for Platinum Equity. 
Read more...



Christian Cook
Principal
Christian Cook is responsible for managing the transition of newly acquired companies into Platinum Equity’s portfolio.
Read more...



Adam Cooper
Principal

Adam Cooper is responsible for aspects of financial due diligence and also often leads the structuring and execution of acquisition and divestiture transactions. As a member of the operating committee for certain portfolio companies, he also has responsibilities related to post-acquisition monitoring and oversight of financial performance.

Read more...



Bibi Di Serio
Principal
Bibi Di Serio is responsible for legal and compliance
diligence on Platinum Equity’s M&A Operations team.
Read more...



David Glatt
Principal
David Glatt is responsible for the structuring and execution of 
acquisition and divestiture transactions. He also has responsibilities 
related to post-acquisition monitoring and oversight of operational 
performance at certain portfolio companies.
Read more...



Soo Jin Goh
Principal
Soo Jin Goh is co-head of Platinum Equity’s team based in Singapore.
Read more...



Todd Golditch
Principal
Todd Golditch is responsible for the structuring and execution of 
acquisition and divestiture transactions. He also has responsibilities 
related to post-acquisition monitoring and oversight of operational 
performance at certain portfolio companies.
Read more...



Roger House
Principal

Roger House is responsible for evaluating operational turnaround opportunities in the hospitality industry and in other sectors where real estate provides a strong element of downside protection to the investment thesis. 

Read more...



Robert Klap
Principal
Robert Klap is based in Platinum Equity’s London office and is involved in the firm’s deal origination and investor relations activities.
Read more...



Dan Krasner
Principal
Dan Krasner is responsible for the structuring and execution of acquisition 
and divestiture transactions. As a member of the operating committees for 
portfolio companies, he also has responsibilities related to post-acquisition 
monitoring and oversight of add-on and divestiture transactions.
Read more...



Renee Koontz
Principal
Renee Koontz is responsible for managing the transition of newly acquired companies into Platinum Equity’s portfolio.
Read more...



Jason LaDuke
Principal
Jason LaDuke is responsible for managing the transition of newly acquired
companies into Platinum Equity’s portfolio. He also has responsibilities
related to post-transition monitoring and oversight of operational performance
at certain portfolio companies.
Read more...



Matt Louie
Principal
Matt Louie is responsible for the structuring and execution of 
acquisition and divestiture transactions. He also has responsibilities 
related to post-acquisition monitoring and oversight of operational 
performance at certain portfolio companies.
Read more...



Aaron Mazzolini
Principal
Aaron Mazzolini is responsible for divestiture transactions for the firm  from front-end through closing. His duties include the marketing,  negotiation and execution of strategic divestitures. 
Read more...



Scott McCarthy
Principal
Scott McCarthy is responsible for financial due diligence and supports the 
structuring and execution of acquisition and divestiture transactions. As a 
member of the operating committee for certain portfolio companies, he also has 
responsibilities related to post-acquisition monitoring and oversight of 
financial performance
Read more...



Mike Scott
Principal
Mike Scott takes responsibility for leading a team that transitions new acquisitions into the portfolio. 
Read more...



Kevin P. Smith
Principal
Kevin P. Smith is Head of Debt Capital Markets and is responsible for all debt capital placement and related corporate finance activity for new and existing portfolio companies. 
Read more...



Roger Thibault
Principal
Roger Thibault is responsible for evaluating technology-related aspects  of prospective additions to the Platinum Equity portfolio.
Read more...



Farhaad Wadia
Principal
Farhaad Wadia is responsible for the structuring and execution of 
acquisition and divestiture transactions.
Read more...



Mark Wiesenthal
Principal
Mark Wiesenthal is responsible for evaluating operational turnaround opportunities in the hospitality industry and other sectors in which real estate provides an element of downside protection to the investment thesis. He is a member of the group responsible for the acquisitions and operations of Platinum Equity’s hotel portfolio. 
Read more...



Eric Worley
Principal
Eric Worley is responsible for financial due diligence and supports the structuring and execution of acquisition and divestiture transactions. As a member of the operating committee for certain portfolio companies, he also has responsibilities related to post-acquisition monitoring and oversight of financial performance.
Read more...



Marc Yassinger
Principal
Marc Yassinger is a member of the firm’s in-house tax department and is responsible for addressing tax issues relating to the firm’s M&A activities as well as the operations of the firm’s portfolio companies.
Read more...



Steve Zollo
Principal
Steve Zollo is a senior member of Platinum’s M&A Operations team and is responsible for the Corporate IT function and Group Purchasing Program. 
Read more...










